  "features": [
    "ARM Cortex-M4F at 64 MHz",
    "Native USB 2.0 Full Speed",
    "BLE 5.1 with direction finding",
    "512KB Flash, 128KB RAM",
    "42 GPIOs (QFN48 package)",
    "Cheaper than nRF52840 ($2.50-3.50 vs $5+)",
    "Thread/Zigbee 802.15.4 support",
    "NFC-A tag support",
    "Lower power consumption than nRF52840",
    "Used in BBC micro:bit v2"
  ],
  "concerns": [
    "Half the flash and RAM of nRF52840 — may limit complex firmware",
    "No established keyboard dev boards — requires custom PCB",
    "Fewer community resources than nRF52840 for keyboards",
    "128KB RAM is tight for ZMK with many features enabled",
    "Requires external antenna design",
    "Requires SWD programmer for bootloader flash",
    "QFN package requires reflow soldering"
  ],
  "designNotes": [
    "Good cost-optimized alternative to nRF52840 for production keyboards",
    "512KB flash is sufficient for most ZMK builds without extras",
    "128KB RAM is workable but limits simultaneous BLE connections",
    "BLE 5.1 direction finding is not useful for keyboards but indicates newer silicon",
    "Consider this for cost-sensitive designs where full nRF52840 is overkill",
    "Needs custom ZMK board definition",
    "QFN40 package is easier to route than nRF52840's QFN73"
  ],
